s4_title:'Universe Viewer',s4_intro:'Real-time visualization of DMX channel data.',s4_operation_title:'How to Use',s4_op_step1:'Select universes to display from the universe picker at the top (multi-select supported).',s4_op_step2:'Use Select All / Deselect All for batch operations.',s4_op_step3:'Displaying 16 or more universes simultaneously may affect performance.',s4_grid_title:'Channel Grid',s4_grid1:'Displays 512 channels in a color-coded grid',s4_grid2:'Higher values appear brighter (black to blue to cyan to white gradient)',s4_grid3:'Value display format is configurable in Settings:',s4_th_format:'Format',s4_th_range:'Range',s4_merge_title:'Merge Conflict Display',s4_merge_desc:'When multiple sources are sending to the same universe, the number of conflicting channels and source IPs are displayed.',
s5_title:'Device Discovery',s5_intro:'Automatically discover and manage DMX devices on the network.',s5_filter_title:'Filter Tabs',s5_filter_desc:'Filter devices by category: All / Art-Net / sACN / Cluster / Computers / Other. Use the search box to filter by IP address, hostname, or MAC address.',s5_info_title:'Device Information',s5_th_col:'Column',s5_th_content:'Content',s5_col1:'Online status (green = connected, gray = offline)',s5_col2:'Device IP address',s5_col3:'Hostname (custom name can be set)',s5_col4:'MAC address',s5_col5:'Art-Net / sACN / Cluster / Computer / Network',s5_col6:'Universe count, firmware version, port count',s5_custom_title:'Custom Names',s5_custom_desc:'Click the pencil icon next to the hostname to assign a custom name. Custom names persist across application restarts.',s5_scan_title:'Network Scan',s5_scan_desc:'Click the Network Scan button to run an active network scan.',
