s8_title:'Settings',s8_network_title:'Network Settings',s8_network_single:'<strong>Single Interface mode</strong> (default): Select a network interface from the dropdown. Choose "All Interfaces (0.0.0.0)" to listen on all interfaces.',s8_network_multi:'<strong>Multi-NIC mode</strong>: Configure Art-Net/sACN enabled/disabled per interface. See the Multi-NIC section for details.',s8_protocol_title:'Protocol Settings',s8_th_setting:'Setting',s8_th_default:'Default',s8_th_desc:'Description',s8_th_options:'Options',s8_p1_name:'Art-Net Enabled',s8_p1_desc:'Art-Net protocol reception',s8_p2_name:'Art-Net Port',s8_p2_desc:'Art-Net listen port',s8_p3_name:'sACN Enabled',s8_p3_desc:'sACN (E1.31) protocol reception',s8_p4_name:'sACN Port',s8_p4_desc:'sACN listen port',s8_p5_name:'sACN Universes',s8_p5_desc:'sACN universes to receive (comma-separated)',s8_display_title:'Display Settings',s8_disp1_name:'UI Update Rate',s8_disp1_opts:'15 fps (low CPU) / 30 fps (recommended) / 60 fps (smooth)',s8_disp2_name:'Universe Number Format',s8_disp2_opts:'Decimal(1), Decimal(0), Hex, Art-Net(Net:Sub:Uni), ASCII',s8_disp3_name:'Channel Number Format',s8_disp3_opts:'Decimal(1), Decimal(0), Hex',s8_disp4_name:'Channel Value Format',s8_disp4_opts:'Decimal (0-255), Hex (00-FF), Percent (0-100%)',s8_merge_title:'Merge Settings',s8_merge1:'HTP / LTP / Priority (see Merge Engine section)',s8_merge2:'Time before an unresponsive source is excluded (1000-60000 ms)',
s9_title:'Advanced: Merge Engine',s9_intro:'Configure how signals from multiple sources on the same universe are combined.',s9_th_mode:'Mode',s9_th_behavior:'Behavior',s9_htp:'Highest Takes Precedence \u2014 adopts the highest value for each channel. Prevents unintended fade-out leaks.',s9_ltp:'Latest Takes Precedence \u2014 adopts the most recently received value for each channel. Reflects the latest operation.',s9_priority:'Source priority-based selection. Falls back to HTP when sources share the same priority.',s9_note1:'<strong>Global setting</strong>: Select a common merge mode for all universes on the Settings page.',s9_note2:'<strong>Per-universe setting</strong>: Apply a different merge mode to specific universes only.',s9_note3:'<strong>Source timeout</strong>: Sources that stop sending packets for the specified duration are automatically excluded.',
s10_title:'Advanced: Multi-NIC',s10_intro:'Receive signals independently on multiple network interfaces.',s10_usecase_title:'Use Cases',s10_uc1:'Separate networks for Art-Net and sACN',s10_uc2:'Simultaneously receive signals from different subnets',s10_uc3:'Redundant backup network configuration',s10_setup_title:'Setup Procedure',s10_step1:'Switch to Multi-NIC mode on the Settings page.',s10_step2:'Enable Art-Net / sACN for each interface.',s10_step3:'Click Apply NIC Config.',s10_tip:'Signals received on each NIC are automatically combined by the merge engine.',
s11_title:'Advanced: Cluster / Redundancy',s11_intro:'Build a cluster with two or more ArtNet Manager instances for automatic failover.',s11_roles_title:'Roles',s11_th_role:'Role',s11_th_behavior:'Behavior',s11_primary:'Actively forwards signals. Source of configuration changes.',s11_standby:'Signal forwarding is muted. Automatically promoted when PRIMARY fails.',s11_flow_title:'Operation Flow',s11_flow1:'On startup, peers are automatically discovered (DISCOVERING state).',s11_flow2:'Roles are assigned (INIT to PRIMARY or STANDBY).',s11_flow3:'Configuration changes on PRIMARY are automatically synced to STANDBY.',s11_flow4:'If PRIMARY health degrades, STANDBY is automatically promoted (PROMOTING to PRIMARY).',s11_ops_title:'Operations',s11_op1:'Monitor cluster status on the Dashboard or header bar.',s11_op2:'Use Force Role to manually switch roles.',s11_op3:'Toggle Auto Sync on or off as needed.',
s12_title:'Advanced: Guardian Mode',s12_intro:'Automatically restarts the application when it terminates unexpectedly.',s12_behavior_title:'Behavior',s12_b1:'Automatically restarts after normal termination or crash (approximately 2 seconds).',s12_b2:'A GUARDIAN badge is displayed in the header bar.',s12_b3:'If the renderer process crashes, signal processing continues and the UI auto-reloads after 2 seconds.',s12_shutdown_title:'Permanent Shutdown',s12_shutdown_note:'Normal window close or Quit operations will be overridden by Guardian, and the app will restart.',s12_shutdown_how:'To completely stop the application:',s12_shutdown1:'Menu: ArtNet Manager \u2192 Permanent Shutdown',s12_shutdown2:'Keyboard shortcut: Ctrl+Shift+Q (Mac: Cmd+Shift+Q)',s12_shutdown3:'After the confirmation dialog, the Guardian is suppressed and the app fully terminates.',
s13_title:'Troubleshooting',s13_nosignal_title:'Not Receiving Signals',s13_th_check:'Check',s13_th_solution:'Solution',s13_r1_check:'Network Interface',s13_r1_fix:'Verify the correct interface is selected in Settings. Use "0.0.0.0" to listen on all interfaces.',s13_r2_check:'Firewall',s13_r2_fix:'Ensure Art-Net (UDP 6454) / sACN (UDP 5568) are allowed.',s13_r3_check:'Protocol Enabled',s13_r3_fix:'Verify Art-Net / sACN are enabled on the Settings page.',s13_r4_check:'Subnet',s13_r4_fix:'Confirm you are on the same subnet as the sender, or that broadcast/multicast traffic can reach you.',s13_r5_check:'sACN Universes',s13_r5_fix:'For sACN, you must specify which universe numbers to receive on the Settings page.',s13_noforward_title:'Forwarding Not Working',s13_f1_check:'Destination Toggle',s13_f1_fix:'Verify the destination is enabled (ON) on the Forwarding page.',s13_f2_check:'Target IP',s13_f2_fix:'Confirm the target IP address is correct and reachable.',s13_f3_check:'Universe Matching',s13_f3_fix:'In "Selected Only" mode, ensure the target universes are included in the overrides.',s13_f4_check:'Cluster Role',s13_f4_fix:'STANDBY nodes do not forward signals. Confirm the node is PRIMARY.',s13_f5_check:'Universe Offset',s13_f5_fix:'Ensure the offset does not push the target universe outside the valid protocol range.',s13_f6_check:'Rate Limit',s13_f6_fix:'Output is capped at 44 Hz. With zero delay, high-frequency input may be throttled.',s13_perf_title:'Poor Performance',s13_p1_check:'UI Update Rate',s13_p1_fix:'Reduce to 15 fps in Settings to lower CPU load.',s13_p2_check:'Universe Display Count',s13_p2_fix:'Displaying 16+ universes simultaneously may cause slowdowns.',s13_p3_check:'Memory Usage',s13_p3_fix:'Check on the Dashboard. Large delay buffers may be the cause.',s13_p4_check:'Delay Buffers',s13_p4_fix:'Large delay values (>1000 ms) increase buffer memory consumption.',s13_cluster_title:'Cluster Issues',s13_c1_check:'Network',s13_c1_fix:'Ensure both nodes are on the same network segment and can communicate.',s13_c2_check:'Status Check',s13_c2_fix:'Verify that the peer appears in the Dashboard cluster section.',s13_c3_check:'Config Sync',s13_c3_fix:'Confirm Auto Sync is enabled and Config Hash matches.',s13_c4_check:'Manual Override',s13_c4_fix:'Use Force Role to manually switch PRIMARY/STANDBY for testing.',s13_guardian_title:'Cannot Fully Stop Guardian Mode',s13_g1:'Use Permanent Shutdown from the menu, or press Ctrl+Shift+Q (Mac: Cmd+Shift+Q).',s13_g2:'Normal window close or Quit (Ctrl+Q) will be intercepted by Guardian and the app will restart.',s13_merge_title:'Merge Conflict Warnings',s13_m1:'This indicates multiple sources are sending to the same universe.',s13_m2:'Select an appropriate merge mode (HTP/LTP/Priority) on the Settings page.',s13_m3:'You can also apply a different merge mode to specific universes only.',
